          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Semantic Zoom (Fragment Distance)\n\nUse focus-distance semantics with no edge-specific controls in v1.\n\n- Distance 0 (active fragment): detail card\n- Distance 1 (adjacent fragments): summary card\n- Distance >=2 (older/far fragments): dot node\n\nImplementation notes:\n\n1. Compute distance from active fragment/root.\n2. Derive semantic level from distance first, camera zoom second.\n3. Render nodes by level (`detail` | `summary` | `dot`).\n4. Keep edge rendering simple for now: no semantic edge controls.\n\nAcceptance:\n\n- Switching active fragment updates levels deterministically.\n- Dot/summarized nodes remain selectable.\n- Existing graphs remain backward compatible.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
