    {
      "id": "task-save-policy",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Save Policy (Graph vs Fragment)",
      "position": {
        "x": 2874.833333333333,
        "y": -1667.2463113334816
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Save Policy: Fragment-Scoped Persistence\n\nDecision for this phase:\n\n## Save\n- Save writes the current fragment only.\n- A `.node` file is a fragment artifact, not the whole visible session.\n- Expanded neighboring fragments are not part of the save scope.\n\n## Export\n- Export can be selection-based, but only within the current fragment.\n- Cross-fragment selection is not a valid persistence scope.\n- If selection includes foreign-fragment nodes, export should reject with a clear message.\n\n## Implication\n- Visibility does not widen persistence scope.\n- If a node belongs in the current fragment, author it into the fragment explicitly.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
