    {
      "id": "task-dictionary-security",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Host Dictionary Security Policy",
      "position": {
        "x": 3359.833333333333,
        "y": -1147.2463113334816
      },
      "width": 600,
      "height": 420,
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Host Dictionary Security Policy\n\nFor fragment expansion: merge metadata, not executable trust.\n\n## Default Import Mode\n\n- Imported dictionary entries are `untrusted` by default.\n- Merge type metadata and references, but do **not** auto-enable execution features.\n\n## Entry Security Flags\n\nEach imported entry should include:\n\n- `originRef`\n- `originHash` (if available)\n- `trust`: `untrusted | trusted`\n- `capabilities` object (render/edit/script/lifecycle)\n\n## Capability Defaults (Untrusted)\n\n- `render: true` (safe subset)\n- `edit: false`\n- `script: false`\n- `lifecycle: false`\n\n## Promotion Flow\n\n- User can explicitly promote an entry (or source) to `trusted`.\n- Promotion should be explicit in UI and persisted intentionally.\n- Trust should be pinned to `originRef + originHash` when possible.\n\n## Host Protection\n\n- Manifest policy should default to `allowImportedExecution: false`.\n- Fragment expansion must not silently change host runtime behavior.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Expanding untrusted fragments cannot run script/lifecycle code.\n- Host graph remains deterministic unless user explicitly trusts imports.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
