          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Expansion Scope: One-Hop Only\n\nDecision for Q3:\n\n- Traversing a composition link expands **exactly one** referenced fragment.\n- Expansion is one-hop only in v1 (no recursive chain expansion).\n\nClarification:\n\n- One expansion can materialize multiple nodes/edges (the fragment content).\n- But only one external fragment is resolved per traverse action.\n\nSafety limits:\n\n- Enforce per-expansion caps (max nodes, max edges).\n- Reject expansion with explicit error if caps are exceeded.\n\nAcceptance:\n\n- A single traverse action cannot pull nested downstream fragments automatically.\n- User must explicitly trigger the next hop from newly materialized references.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
