      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Q5 Decision: UI Parity + Execution Boundary\n\nDecision status: implemented enough for this phase.\n\n- `port` and `graph-reference` expose the same target semantics in UI.\n- Shared fields: `target.kind`, `target.mode`, `target.ref`, `entryPort`, trust/policy flags.\n- Node rendering differs, but composition semantics stay consistent.\n\nExecution boundary:\n\n- `mode=navigate`: open target graph in its own host session.\n- `mode=expand`: import into host as projected structure with downgraded authority.\n- `mode=bridge`: create an explicit local capability without ambient authority transfer.\n- visible content does not gain execution authority unless focus later moves there.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
