    {
      "id": "task-attach-layout-policy",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Attach/Layout Policy (Hybrid)",
      "position": {
        "x": 6720,
        "y": 500
      },
      "width": 740,
      "height": 440,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Attach/Layout Policy (Hybrid)\n\nAdopt a simple default with optional polish:\n\n## Default (v1): Lane Attach + Deterministic Nudge\n\n- Attach fragment root near source node using source port side.\n- Reserve lanes per `sourceNodeId + side`.\n- New expansions use next lane index (stable ordering).\n- Preserve fragment internal relative coordinates.\n- Apply bounded collision nudge only when overlap exceeds threshold.\n- Do not auto-move host-authored existing nodes.\n\n## Optional (user-invoked): Reflow Branch\n\n- Provide explicit action to reflow injected branch for cleaner layout.\n- Reflow only the injected branch (not entire host graph).\n\n## Suggested parameters\n\n- `laneGapPx`: 220\n- `attachMarginPx`: 80\n- `maxNudgePx`: 240\n- `collisionPaddingPx`: 24\n- `fallbackSide`: opposite of preferred side if blocked\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Repeated expansions from same source are spatially stable.\n- Branches do not overlap by default in common cases.\n- Reflow action improves crowded branches without disturbing host layout.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
