    {
      "id": "task-remote-trust-gating-v1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Remote Ref Trust Gating (V1 Final)",
      "position": {
        "x": 7480,
        "y": 500
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Remote Ref Trust Gating (V1 Final)\n\n## 1) Protocol allowlist\n\n- Allow: `github://`, `https://`\n- Block: `file://`, `javascript:`, `data:`\n- `http://` blocked except localhost/dev mode (optional host setting).\n\n## 2) Integrity pinning\n\n- Compute `originHash = sha256(rawFetchedContent)` on import.\n- Store on imported metadata with `originRef`.\n- If same ref later resolves to different hash: treat as new untrusted version.\n\n## 3) Resource limits (modest defaults)\n\n- Fetch timeout: `8s`\n- Max payload bytes: `1.5 MB`\n- Max nodes per expansion: `250`\n- Max edges per expansion: `500`\n- Max external loads per action: `1` (one-hop rule)\n\n## 4) Validation gates\n\n- Require valid `nodegraph-data` shape before merge.\n- Reject malformed ports/edges/required fields.\n- Imported executable sections disabled unless trusted.\n\n## 5) Trust scope\n\n- Trust is graph-scoped in v1 (current graph only).\n\n## 6) User prompt behavior\n\n- First import of source: default to **Import passive only**.\n- Optional action: **Trust this version** (hash-pinned).\n- If hash changes later: revert to passive and warn.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Web refs remain usable (`https://`) with explicit safety rails.\n- No silent execution from imported remote content in host context.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
