    {
      "id": "task-trust-persistence-v1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Trust Metadata Persistence (V1)",
      "position": {
        "x": 9000,
        "y": 500
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 460,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "any",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Trust Metadata Persistence (V1)\n\nDecision: persist trust metadata in the graph file, graph-scoped only.\n\n## Trust binding\n\n- Trust is pinned to `originRef + originHash` (not ref alone).\n- If content hash changes, trust does not carry automatically.\n\n## Storage model\n\n- Prefer centralized registry:\n- `manifest.data.settings.trustRegistry`\n- (instead of duplicating trust flags on every dictionary entry)\n\n## Suggested trust record shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"originRef\": \"github://owner/repo/path/file.node\",\n  \"originHash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"trust\": \"trusted\",\n  \"trustedAt\": \"2026-03-13T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"trustedBy\": \"user\",\n  \"capabilities\": {\n    \"render\": true,\n    \"edit\": false,\n    \"script\": false,\n    \"lifecycle\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Behavior\n\n1. Import creates untrusted record by default.\n2. User promotion marks exact `ref+hash` trusted.\n3. Re-import with changed hash creates new untrusted version.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Trust is explicit, auditable, and portable with graph file.\n- No silent trust inheritance on content changes.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
